student initiatives stanford public interest law foundation stanford public interest law foundation est 1978 student initiatives have a good idea for a public interest initiative at stanford or one outside of stanford that involves stanford students the stanford public interest law foundation spilf funds student projects and initiatives that seek to make a public interest impact in our communities and applications can come from both well established student initiatives and new ones that need spilf funding to get off the ground in the past spilf has funded tax assistance to the poor and provided financial support to students participating in the alternative spring break project check back soon for the application for the next round of 2012 funding for student initiatives also if you have more questions about the projects or the application feel free to fill out the form under contact us search for about spilf support spilf bid for justice auction fellowships student initiatives grants contact us information for alumni purchase tickets auction news february 27 2012 and the theme is in celebration of the twentieth anniversary of the bid for justice auction the planning committees have announced the theme for 2012 the roaring twenties check out the new auction themed logo below sls news february 16 2012 stanford law school mourns the loss of david l rosenhan professor of law & psychology emeritus february 13 2012 stanford law school advances new model for legal education the student voice for public interest at sls 2012 spilf
